cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.TY, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the intersection of two important concepts in programming languages: generalized algebraic datatypes (GADTs) and subtyping. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO) as it involves studying the soundness of variance annotations in GADT definitions. It also touches upon software engineering (cs.SE) as it raises interesting design questions. Additionally, it may fall under type theory (cs.TY) and computation and language (cs.CL) as it deals with subtyping constraints and their impact on GADTs.
